  "texts": [
    "Large language models (LLMs) have become the state of the art in most if not all natural language processing (NLP) and natural language understanding (NLU) tasks.",
    "Since the publication of the transformer architecture by Vaswani et al (2017), several authors and com-panies have made use of (variations of) this architecture to tackle tasks such as translation, summarization, question answering, sentiment analysis, or text generation.",
    "Whereas the original transformer consisted of an encoder-decoder architecture, variations of this have been introduced in subsequent works.",
    "Namely, encoder-only architectures such as BERT (Devlin et al 2018) -used mostly for text classification-, decoder-only architectures such as GPT (Radford et al 2018) -for text generation-, and encoder-decoder architectures, such as T5 (Raffel et al 2020) -for text-to-text processing, such as translation-.",
    "The training of LLMs occurs in different phases."
  ],
